    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Breakpoint Strategy Tips",
      "text": "For easy crackmes, strcmp, strncmp, memcmp, and strlen are usually the highest-value breakpoints because they often expose expected data, input data, and compare lengths. When a breakpoint hits, inspect function argument registers first, then follow the memory they point to with x/s or x/16xb. After the function returns, inspect RAX because 0 often means equality for compare functions. If you see a hidden success string in puts or printf, backtrace and inspect the preceding compare/jump logic."
    },
